  <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold mb-6 text-center" style="font-family: 'Google Sans Code';">
    CapCut vs Adobe Premiere Pro: Can a Free App Really Beat a Pro Editor?
  </h1>

  <p class="text-gray-300 text-lg leading-relaxed mt-6">
    When it comes to video editing, you’ve probably heard about <strong>CapCut</strong> and <strong>Adobe Premiere Pro</strong>. One is a free, mobile-friendly app perfect for quick edits, while the other is a professional software used by studios and filmmakers worldwide. But the question that many content creators ask is: <em>Can a free app like CapCut actually compete with a pro editor like Premiere Pro?</em> Let’s dive in.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 text-white">Ease of Use</h2>
  <p class="text-gray-400 text-base leading-relaxed mt-2">
    Honestly, CapCut is incredibly beginner-friendly. Its interface is simple and intuitive, making it super easy to edit short videos, TikToks, or Instagram Reels. Adobe Premiere Pro, on the other hand, is packed with features and can feel overwhelming if you’re just starting out. I personally prefer CapCut for quick edits because I don’t have to spend hours learning the software.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 text-white">Features & Tools</h2>
  <p class="text-gray-400 text-base leading-relaxed mt-2">
    Premiere Pro is packed with professional tools — multi-track editing, color grading, motion graphics, and seamless integration with other Adobe apps like After Effects. CapCut doesn’t have all of that, but it does come with trendy templates, filters, transitions, and even AI-powered tools like background removal. For my projects, CapCut has everything I need, and honestly, it’s fast and convenient.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 text-white">Platforms & Accessibility</h2>
  <p class="text-gray-400 text-base leading-relaxed mt-2">
    CapCut is free and available on both mobile and desktop, which makes it super accessible. Adobe Premiere Pro requires a paid subscription and a fairly powerful computer. Since I don’t have a high-end system, CapCut works perfectly for me without slowing my computer down.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 text-white">Cost Factor</h2>
  <p class="text-gray-400 text-base leading-relaxed mt-2">
    Here’s the biggest advantage of CapCut — it’s completely free! Adobe Premiere Pro costs a subscription every month. For creators like me who are just starting out or want to save on software, CapCut gives you all the essential editing tools without spending a single rupee.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 text-white">My Take</h2>
  <p class="text-gray-400 text-base leading-relaxed mt-2">
    If you’re a professional filmmaker working on long, cinematic projects, Premiere Pro is still the king. But for everyday creators who want <strong>fast, easy, and free editing</strong>, CapCut is honestly amazing. I use it myself because it doesn’t need a high-spec computer, and it gets the job done without any extra cost. For many creators in 2025, CapCut is more than enough to create engaging videos.
  </p>
